&lt;p&gt;The website running on 80 has…&lt;em&gt;nothing&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;: it’s a bare Apache placeholder.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At this point I admit to having been stumped: no amount of fuzzing or
content-discovery turned up anything relevant.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;…until I considered the name of the box: &lt;em&gt;UnderPass&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;. UnDerPass. UDP.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FFS…&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the sake of brevity (UDP scans are sloooooow), there’s one port open:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;sh&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-sh &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-sh&quot; data-lang=&quot;sh&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;❯&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; sudo nmap&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt; -sU -p&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; 161&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt; -Pn -sCV&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; 10.10.11.48
