&lt;h2 id=&quot;dot-matrix-destruction&quot;&gt;Dot-Matrix Destruction&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I wanted to buy one of those squeaky old printers from this vintage printer
company, but they’re all so overpriced. Forget that. Can you just have them
print out the flag for us?&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The flag is at &lt;code&gt;&#x2F;flag.txt&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The challenge spawns a container at &lt;code&gt;http:&#x2F;&#x2F;py42aoqa.chals.mctf.io&#x2F;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;. There’s
no obvious SQLi or similar but the input is XML so…XXE time!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There’s a fairly standard LFI via XXE. That allows files to be &lt;em&gt;read&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; but how
to actual present the contents of that file? Thankfully, if an invalid
&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;country&amp;gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; element is passed, the invalid data are presented in the resulting
error message, allowing the LFI to be similarly displayed:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;sh&quot; style=&quot;background-color:#2b303b;color:#c0c5ce;&quot; class=&quot;language-sh &quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-sh&quot; data-lang=&quot;sh&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#bf616a;&quot;&gt;curl&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; http:&#x2F;&#x2F;py42aoqa.chals.mctf.io&#x2F;api&#x2F;search_printers \
